- Fri 14 Dec 2018. Comment on Dashboard
[Crofs blog, edited]
https://crofsblogs.typepad.com/h5n1/2018/12/ebola-a-small-worrying-number.html

The Ministry of Health (MoH) and WHO AFRO run the informative Ebola DRC KIVU 2018 Dashboard, which is usually a day or 2 late but provides a good overview of the situation. One statistic, however, seems to stay about the same: the number of Ebola contacts who have not been traced.

All told, 6400 persons are considered contacts of Ebola cases, but only 5800 are being monitored. Thus, 600 remain unreached and perhaps unreachable.

Then the MoH reports "community deaths," which are likely the result of untraced contacts, and every one prolongs the fight against the outbreak. Worse yet, some infected contacts could cross the border or travel elsewhere in the DRC, and thereby spread the outbreak even further.

--
